==歷史==

=== 現代化之前的抽水馬桶系統 ===
自[[新石器时代|新石器時代]]以來就存在著各種形式的沖水廁所，[[奥克尼|奧克尼]]的[[斯卡拉布雷新石器时代遗迹|斯卡拉布雷]]是英國最古老的新石器時代村落，大約在公元前31世紀就已經使用一種水力技術的[[卫生设施|衛生設施]]。<ref>{{Citation|title=Clean: a history of personal hygiene and purity|author=Virginia Sarah Smith|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GZBsRv17U3gC&q=Skara%20Brae%20drop%20toilet|access-date=30 July 2010|page=28|isbn=978-0-19-929779-5|year=2007|archive-date=2021-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210902164947/https://books.google.com/books?id=GZBsRv17U3gC&q=Skara%20Brae%20drop%20toilet|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Pre">{{cite journal|title=Provisional Report on the Excavations at Skara Brae, and on Finds from the 1927 and 1928 Campaigns. With a Report on Bones|url=http://journals.socantscot.org/index.php/psas/article/view/7758/7726|first1=V.|last2=Paterson|first2=J.|date=30 November 1929|journal=Proceedings of the Society of Antiquaries of Scotland|last3=Thomas|first3=Bryce|last1=Childe|access-date=6 May 2020|archive-date=2020-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201003105621/http://journals.socantscot.org/index.php/psas/article/view/7758/7726|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Suddath|first1=Claire|title=A Brief History of Toilets|url=http://content.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1940525,00.html|access-date=6 May 2020|agency=Time|publisher=Time|date=19 November 2009|archive-date=2020-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219180926/http://content.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1940525,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Skara Brae|url=https://www.worldhistory.org/Skara_Brae/|access-date=6 May 2020|website=[[World_History_Encyclopedia|World History Encyclopedia]]|last1=Mark|first1=Joshua, J.|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928230454/https://www.ancient.eu/Skara_Brae/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=A STONE-AGE SETTLEMENT AT THE BRAES OF RINYO, ROUSAY, ORKNEY. (FIRST REPORT.)|url=http://soas.is.ed.ac.uk/index.php/psas/article/download/8098/8066|first1=Walter G., F.S.A.ScoT.|last2=Childe|first2=V. G., F.S.A.ScoT.|date=1938|journal=Proceedings of the Society of Antiquaries of Scotland|volume=72|last1=Grant|access-date=6 May 2020|archive-date=2020-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201003074231/http://soas.is.ed.ac.uk/index.php/psas/article/download/8098/8066|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last1=Childe|first1=Vere Gordon|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XI4wAQAAIAAJ&q=drain|title=Skara Brae|last2=Clarke|first2=D. V.|publisher=H.M.S.O., previously: Kegan Paul, Trench, Trubner & Company, Limited|year=1931|location=UK|pages=12, 20, 28|isbn=9780114917555|language=en|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2021-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419172106/https://books.google.com/books?id=XI4wAQAAIAAJ&q=drain|dead-url=no}}</ref>這個村莊的設計是使用一條小溪連接排水系統來沖走髒物。

美索不達米亞人在公元前4000年左右引入粘土下水管道，最早的例子是在[[尼普爾|尼普爾]]的貝爾神廟和[[埃什南纳|埃什南纳]]發現的，<ref name="FLUORIDATED WATER CONTROVERSY">{{cite book|last1=Burke|first1=Joseph|title=FLUORIDATED WATER CONTROVERSY|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fdIoDwAAQBAJ&q=The+Babylonians+introduced+the+world+to+clay+sewer+pipes,+c4000+BCE,+with+the+earliest+examples+found+in+the+Temple+of+Bel+at+Nippur+and+at+Eshnunna,+Babylonia.&pg=PA2|access-date=4 August 2017|isbn=9781365912870|date=24 April 2017|archive-date=2021-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210902164951/https://books.google.com/books?id=fdIoDwAAQBAJ&q=The+Babylonians+introduced+the+world+to+clay+sewer+pipes,+c4000+BCE,+with+the+earliest+examples+found+in+the+Temple+of+Bel+at+Nippur+and+at+Eshnunna,+Babylonia.&pg=PA2|dead-url=no}}</ref>用來清除汙水，並在井中收集雨水。[[烏魯克|烏魯克]]城在公元前3200年出現已知最早的磚砌{{le|簡易廁所|Latrine}}，包括蹲式和坐式廁所。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Mitchell|first=Piers D.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HU6rCwAAQBAJ&q=McMahon,+A.+in+Sanitation,+Latrines+and+Intestinal+Parasites+in+Past+Populations&pg=PA263|title=Sanitation, Latrines and Intestinal Parasites in Past Populations|date=3 March 2016|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-05953-0|pages=22|language=en|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2021-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210917030308/https://books.google.com/books?id=HU6rCwAAQBAJ&q=McMahon,+A.+in+Sanitation,+Latrines+and+Intestinal+Parasites+in+Past+Populations&pg=PA263|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The secret history of ancient toilets|url=http://www.nature.com/news/the-secret-history-of-ancient-toilets-1.19960|last=Wald|first=Chelsea|date=26 May 2016|journal=Nature News|issue=7604|doi=10.1038/533456a|volume=533|pages=456–458|language=en|bibcode=2016Natur.533..456W|pmid=27225101|s2cid=4398699|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2020-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803093130/https://www.nature.com/news/the-secret-history-of-ancient-toilets-1.19960|dead-url=no}}</ref>後來[[赫梯|西臺]]城市[[哈图沙|哈圖沙]]使用了粘土管，<ref>{{Cite book|last=Burney|first=Charles|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=azPl5Jzv930C&q=Hattusa+clay+pipes&pg=PA307|title=Historical Dictionary of the Hittites|date=19 April 2004|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-6564-8|language=en|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2021-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210917030338/https://books.google.com/books?id=azPl5Jzv930C&q=Hattusa+clay+pipes&pg=PA307|dead-url=no}}</ref>這些管段易於拆卸和更換，也便於清洗。

公元前3000年，地中海[[克里特島|克里特島]]的[[克諾索斯|克諾索斯]]王宮，被发现有一條撒香水的沟渠上有厕所蹲坑，廁所的屋頂裝有收集[[雨水|雨水]]的蓄水盆，雨水經由彎曲的陶管，緩緩流入樓下的廁所。

公元前2000年，米諾斯文明發展了可沖水坐式馬桶，在[[克诺索斯|克諾索斯]]和阿克羅蒂里挖掘出了一些樣本。<ref>C. Michael Hogan. 2007. [http://www.themodernantiquarian.com/site/10854/knossos.html#fieldnotes ''Knossos fieldnotes'', The Modern Antiquarian] {{Wayback|url=http://www.themodernantiquarian.com/site/10854/knossos.html#fieldnotes|date=20171108021923}}</ref><ref>{{cite encyclopedia|url=https://www.worldhistory.org/thera/|title=Thera|author=Mark Cartwright|encyclopedia=[[World_History_Encyclopedia|World History Encyclopedia]]|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2021-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210902164948/https://www.worldhistory.org/thera/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

公元1世紀到5世紀，羅馬帝國普遍使用公共廁所，污物會流入一級或二級下水道。位於英國[[哈德良长城|哈德良長城]]上的{{le|豪斯泰德碉堡|Housesteads_Roman_Fort}}（Housesteads）的廁所即為保存良好的例子。這種廁所沒有現代意義上的沖水功能，但有源源不斷的流水來沖洗汙物。隨著西羅馬帝國的衰落，這些公共廁所系統逐漸在西歐廢棄，但在拜占庭東羅馬帝國仍在持續使用，有紀錄顯示曾換新廁所管道及修復下水道。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=History of sanitation and hygiene technologies in the Hellenic World|url=https://www.academia.edu/35253971|first1=Stavros|last2=Yapijakis|first2=Christos|journal=Journal of Water Sanitation and Hygiene for Development|issue=2|doi=10.2166/washdev.2017.178|year=2017|volume=7|pages=163–180|language=en|issn=2043-9083|last3=Kaiafa-Saropoulou|first3=Asimina|last4=Antoniou|first4=George|last5=Angelakis|first5=Andreas N.|last1=Yannopoulos|doi-access=free|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2021-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210902164950/https://www.academia.edu/35253971|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在[[伊斯蘭黃金時代|伊斯蘭黃金時代]]（8-14世紀）的[[穆斯林世界|穆斯林世界]]，城市裡有與[[供水|供水]]系統和[[污染物排放控制|廢物處理]][[下水道|下水道]]系統相連的沖水馬桶。例如，埃及的[[福斯塔特|福斯塔特市]]有多層房屋（最多六層），配有沖水馬桶，與[[供水系統|供水系統]]相連，每層都有{{le|煙道|Flue}}負責將汙物輸送到地下渠道。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Colin Chant, David Goodman|title=Pre-Industrial Cities and Technology|date=2005|publisher=Routledge|isbn=1134636202|pages=136–8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hK-EAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA136|access-date=2021-09-02|archive-date=2020-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727122533/https://books.google.com/books?id=hK-EAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA136|dead-url=no}}</ref>
